body.sample:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<application xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:apigee="http://api.apigee.com/wadl/2010/07/" xmlns="http://wadl.dev.java.net/2009/02" xmlns:t="urn:simplegeo:simplegeoresponse" xsi:schemaLocation="http://wadl.dev.java.net/2009/02 http://apigee.com/schemas/wadl-schema.xsd http://api.apigee.com/wadl/2010/07/ http://apigee.com/schemas/apigee-wadl-extensions.xsd">
	<resources base="https://api.enterprise.apigee.com/v1" apigee:displayName="Apigee Enterprise API">
	<!-- API Products -->
		<resource path="organizations/{org_name}/apiproducts">
			<param name="org_name" type="xsd:string" style="template" required="true">
			<doc>A specific organization.</doc>
			</param>
				<method id="listApiProduct" name="GET" apigee:displayName="List API Products">
					<apigee:tags>
					<apigee:tag primary="true">API Products</apigee:tag>
					</apigee:tags>
					<apigee:authentication required="true"/>
					<apigee:example url="organizations/{org_name}/apiproducts"/>
					<doc apigee:url="http://apigee.com/docs/api/api_methods/4-list-api-products">Use the GET method
					to list all of the API products in an organization.
					</doc>
					<request>
						<param name="expand" type="xsd:string" style="query" default="false"/>
					</request>
				</method>
		</resource>
	</resources> 
</application>
